entry.title: [ImprovedDownloadWarnings] Fix logic for no-SB warnings vs SB verdict
entry.content:
This fixes a bug in the previous logic for deciding which download

warning to show on the basis of Safe Browsing state of the profile and

the download. Previously we made the incorrect assumption that if the

profile has no SB, then the download must not have an SB verdict. This

is incorrect because the user can turn off SB after the download is

assigned an SB verdict.



The warning that is displayed (i.e. "suspicious" vs "unverified") should

be determined by the presence of the SB verdict primarily, not the SB

state of the profile. This CL switches the order of those checks so that

the warning is primarily determined by the SB verdict, and secondarily

by the state of the profile.

entry.title: Don't allow reportEvent() to send "reserved.*" events.
entry.content:
When calling `window.fence.reportEvent()` passing in just an eventType

string (i.e. the Private Aggregation path), it properly doesn't allow

sending "reserved.*" events, since those eventTypes should only be used

for automatic beacons. This check was never put in for the

`reportEvent()` path that takes in a FenceEvent. This CL adds that check

in place as well as browser-side verification to match what we do for

the Private Aggregation checks.



This CL also prevents registerAdBeacon() from registering a "reserved.*"

event that isn't already defined as a valid automatic beacon event.

entry.title: [Proxy SSLConfig 5/7] SSLConfig::alpn_protos in ConnectJobFactory.
entry.content:
Switch to populating SSLConfig::alpn_protos and

SSLConfig::applications_settings in ConnectJobFactory for

the proxy SSLConfig. These were previously populated further up the

stack, but that is not necessary.



Also explicitly disable H2 in ProxyResolvingClientSocketFactory's

HttpNetworkSession. It was passing in empty SSLConfigs, which

implicitly disables H2, but now that ALPN is copied at a lower layer

from the (bogus) HttpNetworkSession, need to disable it on that

HttpNetworkSession direction.



The combination of the last two paragraphs means that we now try to

negotiate HTTP/1.1 via ALPN when a ProxyResolvingClientSocket is

talking to an SSL proxy (We used to send no ALPN protocols in that

case). This should have no user-visible effect.

entry.title: [ios] Add a moduleLayoutGuide to NTPViewController
entry.content:
This layout guide will initially be used to horizontally lay out all

the NTP "modules", including the MagicStack, the recent tab tile, MVTs,

and the "Feed Containment" module.



Using a layout guide allows the logic for module layout to be

centralized, and allows for easier maintenance of the code and an easier

path to implementing future changes.



Aligning the MagicStack with the layout guide required a number of

changes, in order to allow it to have a width that can change:

* width constraints for modules are added when the module is added

* module width is determined at the time it is needed, because it can

change

* a view was added to mask/clip the MagicStack in landscape, and a

peek offset was used to ensure the module is aligned properly so that

the modules on left and right peeking in looks right

* when the module width changes, the MagicStackScrollView offset needs

to be adjusted so that it is not left in the middle of a page

The Print Document Compositor (nee PDF Compositor) is being extended to

support generating XPS documents for Windows. PDF is still created for

the individual pages (e.g., for Print Preview), while XPS will

optionally be used for the full document which is used for printing to

a destination.

longer have PDF as part of their name. This CL is to just do the

renaming of the calls to be slightly more generic. Further

modifications to enable specifying the desired document type will be in

a follow-up CL.

entry.title: Deflake BFCache test
entry.content:
BackForwardCacheStillLoadingBrowserTest.DoesNotCacheIfFrameStillLoading

is flaky on MSan, and fails more consistently when changing navigation

timing (BlinkSchedulerPrioritizeNavigationIPCs feature).



The failures occur when Unload doesn't have a chance to run in the

initial a.com/controlled renderer. When this happens, the a.com cache

entry doesn't get finalized (as a failure), and the subsequent a.com

request is served out of the memory cache instead of resulting in a

404 from the embedded test server -- which is what the test is

expecting.



To fix this, this CL adds a call to DisableUnloadTimerForTesting() on

a.com's render frame host.

This CL changes instantiations of BackgroundImageGeometry objects into

instantiations of BoxBackgroundPaintContext, while making the later no

longer be a part of the former. BoxPainterBase::PaintFillLayer() now

passed in parameter.



Since the BoxBackgroundPaintContext now provides the means to read

geometric information about the box, the same functionality on

BoxPainterBase (ComputeBorders/ComputePadding) can be removed.



This will allow reusing the majority of BackgroundImageGeometry for

SVGMaskPainter in a future CL.

entry.content:
This matches the current separation in the extensions

process and will make it easier to implement Automation

in ATP.



Since AutomationClient now needs to be bound from Javascript,

adds automation.js as a shim in the AX service V8, and

adds method getDesktop which calls AutomationClient::Enable.



To support getDesktop, copies most of automation_node.js from

the extensions system into automation.js in services/,

so that we have a full chrome.automation.getDesktop

that matches the implementation in extensions.



Note that most functionality in automation.js still needs to

have unittests added, and we'll also need to figure out how

to run existing extension JS tests against ATP. Since this

is not released, testing this functionality is left as a TODO.

entry.title: vt: Fix CHECK trying to merge anonymous block
entry.content:
This CHECK would trip as changing listStylePosition triggers a layout

tree reattachment[1]. This causes the documentElement's LayoutObject to

be removed which happens before the LayoutViewTransitionRoot.



LayoutViewTransitionRoot represents the snapshot containing block and

doesn't have an associated Node, making it "anonymous".



When documentElement's object is removed, it removes itself from the

parent LayoutView. Since LayoutViewTransitionRoot is the only remaining

child, LayoutView tries to hoist its contents onto itself in

CollapseAnonymousBlockChild[2] since anonymous blocks are typically

created artificially to host non-block content in a block flow. This

tries to add the ::view-transition LayoutObject to LayoutView which

trips the CHECK that LayoutView doesn't yet have a

LayoutViewTransitionRoot, since doing so will add one.



LayoutViewTransitionRoot is anonymous but doesn't want to have this

merging/collapsing property so this CL opts it out of that behavior.



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/renderer/core/style/computed_style.cc;l=372;drc=a9187270cee16e9adf8ba3b0286ab80694448a70

[2] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/renderer/core/layout/layout_block_flow.cc;l=271;drc=0e6e802410c16813e03bd2884f8e7f7889b87783

entry.title: [iOS] Add user actions for AuthenticationFlowPerformer dialogs
entry.content:
This patch adds user actions to understand crbug.com/1482623.

The crash is related to an alert dialog. To understand the crash,

for each dialog, 3 user actions are added:

- when the dialog is presented

- when the user confirms the dialog

- when the user cancel the dialog



Those user actions will be used in crash reports with breadcrumbs.

Therefore those user actions cannot be non-user actions.

Once the bug will be fixed, the user actions related to the dialog

being presented will be removed.

Signin_AuthenticationFlowPerformer_ErrorDialog_Confirmed
